\ql{he four }\plain \f1
\fs22
\cf1
{main processes of project procurement management are as follows:\par
}\plain \f1
\fs22
\cf1
{\par
}\plain \f1
\fs22
\cf1
{(1) Planning procurement management involves determining what to procure, when, 
and how. In procurement planning, one must decide what to outsource, determine th
e type of contract, and describe the work for potential sellers. \par
}\plain \f1
\fs22
\cf1
{\par
}\plain \f1
\fs22
\cf1
{(2) Conducting procurements involves obtaining seller responses, selecting selle
rs, and awarding contracts. \par
}\plain \f1
\fs22
\cf1
{\par
}\plain \f1
\fs22
\cf1
{(3) Controlling procurements involves managing relationships with sellers, monit
oring contract performance, and making changes as needed. \par
}\plain \f1
\fs22
\cf1
{\par
}\plain \f1
\fs22
\cf1
{(4) Closing procurements involves completion and settlement of each contract or 
